http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/Youth-killed-in-accident/article14026573.ece

A 21-year-old was crushed to death after a Kerala State Road Transport Corporation (KSRTC) bus ran over him on the Vyttila-Aroor bypass in Kochi on Thursday.The deceased has been identified as Vineeth Vikraman, a native of Konni in Pathanamthitta district.The accident took place around 8.45 a.m. when Vineeth was crossing the National Highway near the Nettur church.Hit by two-wheeler“The victim, an employee of a private firm near here, was first hit by a speeding two-wheeler, and he fell on the road. The bus driver applied brakes but the vehicle had already run over him,” officials said.Vineeth was declared brought dead at a hospital nearby.Case registeredA case has been registered against the person riding the two-wheeler.